📊 Mathematics
Topic: Number System (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
1️⃣ Clear Theory (Easy Language)

Number System is the base of Maths in Railway exams.

It includes:

Types of numbers
Divisibility
Factors & multiples
LCM & HCF basics
Remainders

👉 Many questions come directly or indirectly from this topic.

2️⃣ Types of Numbers
Natural Numbers → 1, 2, 3...
Whole Numbers → 0, 1, 2...
Integers → -2, -1, 0, 1...
Prime Numbers → Only 2 factors (2,3,5,7…)
Composite → More than 2 factors
3️⃣ Important Rules
🔹 Divisibility Rules
2 → Last digit even
3 → Sum of digits divisible by 3
5 → Last digit 0 or 5
9 → Sum divisible by 9
10 → Last digit 0
🔹 HCF & LCM Basics
HCF = Highest common factor
LCM = Lowest common multiple

👉 Product rule:
HCF × LCM = Product of numbers

🔹 Remainder Concept

If a ÷ b →
Dividend = Divisor × Quotient + Remainder

🧠 Quick Tricks
Prime numbers → only 2 factors
Even numbers divisible by 2
LCM = bigger number tendency
HCF = smaller number tendency
